We have the ability to make a difference in the #RealEstate industry, but that can only happen when we all work together to #RestoreOurEarth. Here are a few actionable ideas businesses and individuals can do to make a positive impact.

#EarthDay #GreenWeek

Affordable and workforce housing markets are filled with hard-working residents chasing the American Dream. On #TheWeeklyTake, Avanath Capital Management’s Daryl Carter and #CBRE’s Sarah Garland join Spencer Levy to offer insights on how mission-minded investors are working to expand opportunities. Listen through the link in our bio.

Resident migration patterns are shifting as a result of COVID-19. Using frequently updated USPS data, this report sheds light on where people are choosing to live—and the implications for occupier location and talent strategies and commercial real estate investment decisions. Explore more through the link in our bio.

What are the top 10 trends set to impact the #medicaloffice sector’s recovery in 2021? After COVID-19’s historic impact, CBRE forecasts resilience spurred by employment growth, capital flows and leasing demand. Learn more in the 2021 U.S. Medical Office Trends report via the link in our bio.

Making the case for improving the world, one #investment at a time. On #TheWeeklyTake, Invesco’s Scott Dennis, BentallGreenOak’s Sonny Kalsi and #CBRE Global Investors’ Chuck Leitner join Spencer Levy to explain the ABCs of #ESG capital. Listen to the episode via the link in our bio.

“Take the lead, let your actions define who you are. Embrace the possibility of failure, only then can you learn and grow.” - Linda Johnson, Financial Analyst, Global Finance #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen

"For me, choosing to challenge is about showing up, again and again. It about having the confidence to share your views and move boldly, the grit to weather setbacks and carry on, the passion to inspire both yourself and others – and truly finding the joy of contributing and making an impact. As filmmaker and musician Gina Carey says, “A strong woman looks a challenge dead in the eye and gives it a wink.” - Benji Baer, Chief Marketing Officer #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen

"We are proud of the many women at CBRE who are fundamental to our company's success. They have shown resiliency and strength like never before, managing constant demands under unprecedented circumstances. We are committed to supporting our women by providing opportunities for connection, growth, mentorship and advocacy, as we help advance greater gender equality across the industry." - Lisa Konieczka, Executive Vice President, Advisory & Transaction Services and Chair of CBRE's Women's Network #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen
We will maintain a gender equal mindset. #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen
We will help forge a gender equal world. #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen
We celebrate the many accomplishments of CBRE women on International Women's Day and every day. #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen

“I choose to challenge myself to dream big - whether it’s helping other women to break the glass ceiling, reimagining a digitally enabled future for our industry, or jumping in to solve previously unsolved problems. Now, more than ever, it's important for women to be advocates for women. There are simple things we can do to support each other that will go a long way.” - Chandra Dhandapani, Chief Administrative Officer #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen

“You always hear that inaction is the riskiest response in difficult times. This last year has been a challenging one for many, but for me, with this uncertainty came opportunity, the opportunity to slow down and focus on my priorities -expand my business while also mentoring female talent in our business. I was able to put my plan in to action and it has been tremendously rewarding.” - Sonya Schmidt, Vice President, Advisory & Transaction Services #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen

“I choose to challenge means setting a new standard for leaders and raising the bar for gender inequality. The foundation of future prosperity is built on equality for all and making a difference together! Actions prove who someone is and words just prove who they want to be.” - Edith Chamblin, Senior Business Analyst, Global Workplace Solutions #IWD2021 #ChooseToChallenge #CBREWomen

Bob Sulentic, President and CEO of @cbre, discusses his company's response to COVID-19, support of stakeholders, and the one year anniversary of the Statement on the Purpose of a Corporation:

"I’m particularly proud of the way that our company rallied in support of their colleagues who are facing financial distress as a result of Covid-19. As of late July, we’ve awarded nearly 6,000 grants to CBRE people worldwide who are facing extraordinary expenses or struggling to meet day-to-day needs."

Learn More: https://bit.ly/3kf2b12

#Juneteenth, also known as Freedom Day, serves as an important and timely reminder of how Black people have faced delays in achieving equality, even after laws were passed years before. CBRE will continue to strive for equality as we stand against racism.
